		       G N A T   E X A M P L E S
		       =========================


In order to compile the examples, make sure that the 'gprbuild' command is
in your path. 

Invocation
----------

In order to build the executables provided in this example, you need to
use the "udp_sockets.gpr" project file. On the command-line, do a:

  $ gprbuild -P udp_sockets

In GPS, click on "Build", then "Make" and then "udp_sockets" is compiled, you
can also simply press the F4 key.

Features tested
---------------

* The udp_sockets example shows how to send strings as UDP datagrams
  (udp_client), and how to receive them using a non-blocking socket and
  selector object (udp_server) using GNAT.Sockets.
